TITLE: Attaching SwiftUI onAppear/onDisappear from Parent View
DESCRIPTION: This SwiftUI example demonstrates the flexibility of `onAppear` and `onDisappear` by attaching these modifiers to a child view instance directly within the parent's `body` function, allowing parent views to react to the lifecycle events of their children. It also shows adding a callback to the parent view itself.
SOURCE: https://github.com/ivanvorobei/swiftui/blob/master/Other Projects/React Meets SwiftUI/ComponentDidMount.md#_snippet_2

LANGUAGE: swift
CODE:
```
struct Counter : View {
    @State var count = 0

    func increment () {
        count += 1
    }

    func mount () {
        print("Child mount")
    }

    func unmount () {
        print("Child unmount")
    }

    func parentMount () {
        print("parent mount")
    }


    var body: some View {
        VStack {
            Button(action: increment) {
                Text("Increment")
            }
            if count < 10 || count > 12 {
                ChildCounter(count: count)
                    .onAppear(perform: mount)
                    .onDisappear(perform: unmount)
            }
        }
        .onAppear(perform: parentMount)
    }
}
```

