TITLE: Implementing Counter State SwiftUI (Binding)
DESCRIPTION: Demonstrates using `@Binding` for state management in SwiftUI to enable two-way data flow. The `ContentView` uses `@State` for `count` and passes a binding to it (`$count`) to the `ChildView`. The `ChildView` receives this binding using `@Binding` and can directly modify the `counter` property, which automatically updates the parent's `count` state without requiring a callback closure.
SOURCE: https://github.com/ivanvorobei/swiftui/blob/master/Other Projects/React Meets SwiftUI/State.md#_snippet_2

LANGUAGE: swift
CODE:
```
import SwiftUI

struct ContentView : View {
    @State var count = 0

    var body: some View {
        VStack(spacing: 1.0) {
            Text("Press the button below")
            ChildView(
                counter: $count
            )
        }
    }
}


struct ChildView : View {
    @Binding var counter: Int

    func increment () {
        counter += 1
    }

    var body: some View {
        VStack {
            Text("\(counter)")
            Button(action: increment) {
                Text("Increment")
            }
        }
    }
}
```

----------------------------------------

TITLE: Basic SwiftUI Mount/Unmount with onAppear/onDisappear
DESCRIPTION: This SwiftUI example shows how to use `onAppear` and `onDisappear` view modifiers attached directly to a view to trigger actions when it appears or disappears. It replicates the conditional rendering and lifecycle logging behavior of the React example.
SOURCE: https://github.com/ivanvorobei/swiftui/blob/master/Other Projects/React Meets SwiftUI/ComponentDidMount.md#_snippet_1

LANGUAGE: swift
CODE:
```
import SwiftUI

struct Counter : View {
    @State var count = 0

    func increment () {
        count += 1
    }

    var body: some View {

        VStack {
            Button(action: increment) {
                Text("Increment")
            }
            if count < 10 || count > 12 {
                ChildCounter(count: count)
            }
        }

    }
}

struct ChildCounter : View {
    var count: Int

    func onMount () {
        print("on mount")
    }

    func onUnmount () {
        print("on unmount")
    }

    var body: some View {
        Text("\(count)")
            .onAppear(perform: onMount)
            .onDisappear(perform: onUnmount)
    }
}
```

----------------------------------------

TITLE: Implementing Layout/Content Composition SwiftUI Swift (Text Only)
DESCRIPTION: This SwiftUI example attempts to mirror the React composition pattern by using a closure to pass content to a child view (`Layout`). The `Layout` view's `content` property is currently typed to specifically accept a closure returning a `Text` view, highlighting the challenge of creating a generic layout component that can accept any SwiftUI view type.
SOURCE: https://github.com/ivanvorobei/swiftui/blob/master/Other Projects/React Meets SwiftUI/Children.md#_snippet_1

LANGUAGE: swift
CODE:
```
import SwiftUI

struct Page : View {
    var body: some View {
        Layout() {
            Text("This is the page content")
        }
    }
}

struct Layout : View {

    var content: () -> Text

    var body: some View {
        VStack {
            Text("This is the layout")
            content()
        }
    }
}

```

