TITLE: Using React cloneElement for Child Modification (JSX)
DESCRIPTION: Shows how a parent React component (`LayoutElement`) uses `React.cloneElement` to pass additional props (`style`) to its child component, dynamically modifying its appearance. Requires React dependency. The `LayoutElement` accepts `children` and applies styles using `cloneElement`.
SOURCE: https://github.com/ivanvorobei/swiftui/blob/master/Other Projects/React Meets SwiftUI/CloneElement.md#_snippet_0

LANGUAGE: jsx
CODE:
```
import React from "react";

export function PageElement() {
  return (
    <div>
      <LayoutElement>
        <span>This is the page content</span>
      </LayoutElement>
    </div>
  );
}

export function LayoutElement({ children }) {
  return (
    <div>
      <span>This is the layout</span>
      {React.cloneElement(children, {
        style: {
          fontWeight: "bold",
          fontSize: "2rem"
        }
      })}
    </div>
  );
}
```

----------------------------------------

TITLE: Structuring Swift Code with MARK Comments
DESCRIPTION: This snippet demonstrates the use of `// MARK: - Init` within a Swift class definition. It is used to visually group code related to initialization, improving code readability and navigation according to the project's codestyle guidelines.
SOURCE: https://github.com/ivanvorobei/swiftui/blob/master/CONTRIBUTING.md#_snippet_0

LANGUAGE: Swift
CODE:
```
class Example {

    // MARK: - Init

    init() {}
}
```

